likely issue is with the Correlation Attribute.

Right now:
Correlation Attribute Name = datalake.tag

If datalake.tag value is different for each FlowFile, then MergeRecord treats every file separately and creates multiple output files instead of one merged file.

Recommended Fix:

Add UpdateAttribute processor before MergeRecord
Set:
merge.group = R5EVENTS
In MergeRecord change:
Correlation Attribute Name = merge.group
Update MergeRecord settings:
Merge Strategy = Bin-Packing Algorithm
Minimum Number of Records = 1
Maximum Number of Records = 10000000
Max Bin Age = 1 min
Maximum Number of Bins = 1
Verify all incoming FlowFiles have same merge.group attribute value.
Optionally reduce Max Bin Age from 20 min to 1 min so merge happens faster.

Expected Result:
Multiple CSV files from same source/table will merge into one final CSV file before writing to Azure Blob Storage.
